{"id": "EUVD-2025-6398", "enisaUuid": "a2d4da6c-94c0-3165-8156-2736b74b949e", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/i915/gt: Use spin_lock_irqsave() in interruptible context\n\nspin_lock/unlock() functions used in interrupt contexts could\nresult in a deadlock, as seen in GitLab issue #13399,\nwhich occurs when interrupt comes in while holding a lock.\n\nTry to remedy the problem by saving irq state before spin lock\nacquisition.\n\nv2: add irqs' state save/restore calls to all locks/unlocks in\n signal_irq_work() execution (Maciej)\n\nv3: use with spin_lock_irqsave() in guc_lrc_desc_unpin() instead\n of other lock/unlock calls and add Fixes and Cc tags (Tvrtko);\n change title and commit message\n\n(cherry picked from commit c088387ddd6482b40f21ccf23db1125e8fa4af7e)", "datePublished": "2025-03-12T09:42:04", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:26:39", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-21849", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2bf1f4c129db7a10920655b000f0292f1ee509c2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/47ae46ac5407646420e06b78e0dad331e56a4bb4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e49477f7f78598295551d486ecc7f020d796432e"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-21849", "GHSA-g8v7-wpgp-c9xw"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "09615c62-668a-3e65-9663-d54ea4bc6d9b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "261251f3-a9a8-3694-9562-40251b4b2162", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.17"}, {"id": "3897310a-4ad6-3688-bdf1-2ecbd9e139f2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2f2cc53b5fe7022f3ae602eb24573d52f8740959 <47ae46ac5407646420e06b78e0dad331e56a4bb4"}, {"id": "af30ee4e-86fc-3acb-84c3-60a62b5a8c95", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.9"}, {"id": "baf37363-097f-3e3c-9053-766fac00cd37", "product": {"nam